    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Right now `nvim_get_var` (and variants) don't let you specify a default value in the same way `get` does. On its own this is fine because the calling program can match on the result and apply the default in the error case. However, this means this call cannot be used inside `nvim_call_atomic` since the failure to find the variable will cause the whole atomic operation to fail. A work-around for now is to use `nvim_eval` with `get` but this seems like a limitation worth addressing.",
